00:00:47.859 --> 00:00:49.909
But they CAN donate.

00:00:49.909 --> 00:00:51.729
But does that even make sense?

00:00:51.729 --> 00:00:55.890
MSM populations have blood, we need blood…
why not allow them donation?

00:00:55.890 --> 00:00:57.569
It all comes back to HIV.

00:00:57.569 --> 00:01:02.249
In 1981, a severe disease of epidemic proportions
was spreading through the gay community, killing

00:01:02.249 --> 00:01:04.030
hundreds of thousands of men and women.

00:01:04.030 --> 00:01:08.920
At first, it was called GRID -- gay-related
immunodeficiency disease.

00:01:08.920 --> 00:01:13.759
Later, it was renamed the Acquired Immune
Deficiency Syndrome (AIDS).

00:01:13.759 --> 00:01:18.560
AIDS put the public in a frenzy, and rightly
so.

00:01:18.560 --> 00:01:22.789
229-thousand people died due to AIDS from
1981 to 1992.

00:01:22.789 --> 00:01:27.509
And once it was discovered to be bloodborne,
people realized some had acquired it through

00:01:27.509 --> 00:01:29.220
infected blood transfusion.

00:01:29.220 --> 00:01:34.079
So, the U.S. Food and Drug Administration
decided to act passing a lifetime ban on blood

00:01:34.079 --> 00:01:39.321
donation from any men who had ever had sex
with another man (again known as MSM -- men

00:01:39.321 --> 00:01:42.259
who have sex with men); this was in 1983...

00:01:42.259 --> 00:01:47.140
In 1985, a test called ELISA was invented
which could detect antibodies created by the

00:01:47.140 --> 00:01:52.229
human immune system in response to infection
by the HIV virus which causes AIDS!

00:01:52.229 --> 00:01:57.520
So, now that blood could be screened, we didn't
need the ban, right?

00:01:57.520 --> 00:02:01.850
We just needed to know if someone had HIV,
and screen those who weren't sure!

00:02:01.850 --> 00:02:02.850
Right?

00:02:02.850 --> 00:02:03.850
Nope.

00:02:03.850 --> 00:02:09.509
The Ban remained until 2015, when it was revised
to the current -- abstain from sex for a year,

00:02:09.509 --> 00:02:10.509
bro.

00:02:10.509 --> 00:02:11.509
Then come back.

00:02:11.509 --> 00:02:15.830
Even though, since 1987, HIV blood screening
tests have become nearly 100 percent accurate,

00:02:15.830 --> 00:02:20.349
putting it on par with Hepatitis screening;
MSM populations are still singled out.

00:02:20.349 --> 00:02:25.400
Which is weird, because I'm pretty sure anal
